snippet: Pete Van Wieren, the bespectacled broadcaster who was part of the landmark team that carried Atlanta Braves games throughout the nation on Ted Turner's "SuperStation," died Saturday after a battle with cancer, the team said. He was 69....

headline.print_headline: Longtime Braves Broadcaster Van Wieren Dies at 69
headline.main: Longtime Braves Broadcaster Van Wieren Dies at 69

lead_paragraph: Pete Van Wieren, the bespectacled broadcaster who was part of the landmark team that carried Atlanta Braves games throughout the nation on Ted Turner's "SuperStation," died Saturday after a battle with cancer, the team said. He was 69.
